3. Others that durſt not goe abroad, untill they had cōmitted their Wives,
                  Ant. Dial. to the cuſtody of ſpeciall Keepers;
                  Vide Epiſt. a Dioniſium amicum, in haue rem. which was the caſe of Hypocrates the Phyſitian, when he went to Abder, to viſit Democritus: as alſo the Sophies of Perſia, the Tartarian Mogors, the Kings of China, and the Grand-Senior of the Turkes, Geld yearely innumerable Infants, and keepe Eunuchs, for this purpoſe, even at this Riccius expeditione in Snias, l. 3. c. 9. ſic Lanclavius de rebus Turcicis. day.
